library(tidyverse)
library(gapminder)
package gapminder was built under R version 4.0.5
library(dplyr)

gapminder %>%
  summarize(medianLifeExp = median(lifeExp))

gapminder %>%
  filter(year == 1957) %>%
  summarize( medianLifeExp = median(lifeExp))

gapminder %>%
  filter(year == 1957) %>%
  summarize( medianLifeExp = median(lifeExp), max(gdpPercap))
NA
gapminder %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  summarize(medianLifeExp = median(lifeExp), max(gdpPercap))
gapminder %>%
  filter(year==1957) %>%
  group_by(continent) %>%
  summarize(medianLifeExp = median(lifeExp), max(gdpPercap))
gapminder %>%
  group_by(continent, year) %>%
  summarize(medianLifeExp = median(lifeExp), max(gdpPercap))
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'continent'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
by_year <- gapminder %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  summarize(medianLifeExp = median(lifeExp), max(gdpPercap))

ggplot(by_year, aes(x=year, y=medianLifeExp))+
  geom_point()


by_year_continent <- gapminder %>%
  group_by(continent, year) %>%
  summarize(medianGdpPercap = median(gdpPercap))
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'continent'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
by_year_continent

ggplot(by_year_continent, aes(x=year, y=medianGdpPercap, color=continent))+
  geom_point()

  filter(continent=="Oceania", year==1952)

gapminder_1952 <- gapminder %>%
  filter(year==1952) %>%
  mutate(pop_by_mil = pop / 1000000)

gapminder_1952

ggplot(gapminder_1952, aes(x=pop_by_mil)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 50)

Data manipulation with dplyr


counties <- read_csv("counties.csv")

-- Column specification -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
cols(
  .default = col_double(),
  state = col_character(),
  county = col_character(),
  region = col_character(),
  metro = col_character()
)
i Use `spec()` for the full column specifications.
counties
NA
counties %>%
  select(state, county, population, men, women) %>%
  mutate(proportion_men = men/population) %>%
  filter(population > 10000) %>%
  arrange(desc(proportion_men))

The count verb

Summarizing

counties_selected %>%
  group_by(region, state) %>%
  summarize(total_pop = sum(population)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  summarize(average_pop = mean(total_pop), median_pop= median(total_pop))

`summarise()` has grouped output by 'region'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

The top_n verb

counties_selected %>%
  group_by(region, state) %>%
  summarize(average_income = mean(income)) %>%
  top_n(2, average_income)

`summarise()` has grouped output by 'region'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
counties_selected %>%
  group_by(state, metro) %>%
  summarize(total_pop = sum(population)) %>%
  top_n(1, total_pop) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  count(metro)

`summarise()` has grouped output by 'state'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
